The sons of freedom gathered round, His hostile bands confounded,

And when they’d fain have turned their back, They found themselves surrounded 1

In vain they fought, in vain they fied, Their chief, humane and tender.

Brave St. Clair when he first retired Knew what the fates portended ; And Arnold and heroic Gates His conduct have defended.
